{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01TRKc2Q9QXWDPfeBMq9Z3za","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect. Now I have all the information you need. Here's a comprehensive report with the full contents of each file:\n\n---\n\n## File Contents Report\n\n### 1. **reward-pool-fund.ts** (Handler Implementation)\n`/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/handlers/reward-pool-fund.ts`\n\n```typescript\n/**\n * REWARD_POOL_FUND handler — allocates a share of game fees to the reward pool.\n *\n * Emitted once per settled round. Calculates `floor(feeLamports * reward_pool_fee_share)`\n * and credits the reward pool accounting ledger. Idempotent via UNIQUE(round_id)\n * on reward_pool_fundings.\n */\n\nimport type { Db } from \"../../db.js\";\nimport { logger } from \"../../logger.js\";\n\n// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n// DB helpers\n// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n/** Read a single reward_config value by key. */\nexport async function readRewardConfig(\n  db: Db,\n  key: string,\n): Promise<string | null> {\n  const rows = await db.rawSql<{ value: string }[]>`\n    SELECT value FROM reward_config WHERE key = ${key}\n  `;\n  return rows.length > 0 ? rows[0]!.value : null;\n}\n\n/**\n * Insert a pool funding record. Returns false if a row for this round_id\n * already exists (idempotency guard).\n */\nexport async function insertPoolFunding(\n  db: Db,\n  roundId: string,\n  feeLamports: bigint,\n  fundedLamports: bigint,\n): Promise<boolean> {\n  const rows = await db.rawSql<{ id: string }[]>`\n    INSERT INTO reward_pool_fundings (round_id, fee_lamports, funded_lamports)\n    VALUES (${roundId}, ${feeLamports}, ${fundedLamports})\n    ON CONFLICT (round_id) DO NOTHING\n    RETURNING id\n  `;\n  return rows.length > 0;\n}\n\n/**\n * Atomically increment reward_pool.balance_lamports and lifetime_funded.\n */\nexport async function incrementRewardPool(\n  db: Db,\n  deltaLamports: bigint,\n): Promise<void> {\n  await db.rawSql`\n    UPDATE reward_pool\n    SET balance_lamports = balance_lamports + ${deltaLamports},\n        lifetime_funded  = lifetime_funded + ${deltaLamports},\n        updated_at       = now()\n    WHERE id = 1\n  `;\n}\n\n// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n// Handler factory\n// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\nexport interface RewardPoolFundDeps {\n  db: Db;\n}\n\nexport function createRewardPoolFundHandler(deps: RewardPoolFundDeps) {\n  const { db } = deps;\n\n  return async (payload: Record<string, unknown>): Promise<void> => {\n    const roundId = payload.roundId as string;\n    const feeLamportsStr = payload.feeLamports as string;\n\n    if (!roundId || !feeLamportsStr) {\n      throw new Error(\n        \"reward.pool_fund: malformed payload — missing roundId or feeLamports\",\n      );\n    }\n\n    const feeLamports = BigInt(feeLamportsStr);\n\n    // Read fee share from config\n    const shareStr = await readRewardConfig(db, \"reward_pool_fee_share\");\n    if (!shareStr) {\n      logger.warn(\"reward.pool_fund: reward_pool_fee_share not configured, skipping\", { roundId });\n      return;\n    }\n    const share = parseFloat(shareStr);\n    if (Number.isNaN(share) || share <= 0) {\n      logger.warn(\"reward.pool_fund: invalid reward_pool_fee_share\", { roundId, shareStr });\n      return;\n    }\n\n    // Calculate funded amount: floor(feeLamports * share)\n    // Use Number for the multiplication since share is a float, then BigInt the floor\n    const fundedLamports = BigInt(Math.floor(Number(feeLamports) * share));\n\n    if (fundedLamports <= 0n) {\n      logger.debug(\"reward.pool_fund: funded amount is zero, skipping\", { roundId, feeLamports: feeLamportsStr });\n      return;\n    }\n\n    // Run within a transaction for atomicity\n    await db.withTransaction(async (txDb) => {\n      // Insert funding record (idempotency guard)\n      const inserted = await insertPoolFunding(txDb, roundId, feeLamports, fundedLamports);\n      if (!inserted) {\n        logger.info(\"reward.pool_fund: duplicate round_id, skipping\", { roundId });\n        return;\n      }\n\n      // Increment pool balance\n      await incrementRewardPool(txDb, fundedLamports);\n\n      logger.info(\"reward.pool_fund: pool funded\", {\n        roundId,\n        feeLamports: feeLamportsStr,\n        fundedLamports: fundedLamports.toString(),\n        share,\n      });\n    });\n  };\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. **index.ts** (Handler Registration)\n`/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/index.ts` (lines 1-224)\n\nHandler registration section (lines 206-223):\n\n```typescript\n// Register event handlers before starting the worker\nregisterHandler(\n  EventTypes.REFERRAL_CLAIM_REQUESTED,\n  createClaimHandler({ db, connection, serverKeypair: config.serverKeypair }),\n);\nregisterHandler(\n  EventTypes.REWARD_POOL_FUND,\n  createRewardPoolFundHandler({ db }),\n);\n\n// Event queue worker — processes async side-effects (rewards, notifications, etc.)\nconst eventWorker = createEventWorker(sql, {\n  pollIntervalMs: config.eventQueuePollMs,\n});\neventWorker.start();\nlogger.info(\"Event queue worker started\", {\n  pollIntervalMs: config.eventQueuePollMs,\n});\n```\n\nImports (lines 30-32):\n\n```typescript\nimport { createEventWorker, registerHandler, EventTypes } from \"./queue/index.js\";\nimport { createClaimHandler } from \"./queue/handlers/referral-claim.js\";\nimport { createRewardPoolFundHandler } from \"./queue/handlers/reward-pool-fund.js\";\n```\n\n---\n\n### 3. **event-types.ts** (Event Type Definitions)\n`/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/event-types.ts`\n\n```typescript\n/**\n * Known event type constants for the async event queue.\n *\n * Using a const object + derived union makes typos a compile error\n * instead of a dead event at runtime.\n */\n\nexport const EventTypes = {\n  REFERRAL_CODE_APPLIED: \"referral.code_applied\",\n  REFERRAL_GAME_SETTLED: \"referral.game_settled\",\n  REFERRAL_CLAIM_REQUESTED: \"referral.claim_requested\",\n  GAME_SETTLED: \"game.settled\",\n  REWARD_POOL_FUND: \"reward.pool_fund\",\n  POINTS_GRANT: \"points.grant\",\n  CRATE_DROP: \"crate.drop\",\n  CRATE_SOL_PAYOUT: \"crate.sol_payout\",\n} as const;\n\nexport type EventType = (typeof EventTypes)[keyof typeof EventTypes];\n```\n\nNote: `POINTS_GRANT` is already defined but no handler exists yet.\n\n---\n\n### 4. **db.ts** (DB Client Interface and Patterns)\n`/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/db.ts`\n\n**Key interface (lines 319-678):**\n\n```typescript\nexport interface Db {\n  /** Insert a new round. Throws on duplicate PDA (primary key violation). */\n  insertRound(params: InsertRoundParams): Promise<Round>;\n\n  /** Delete a round by PDA. Returns true if a row was removed. */\n  deleteRoundByPda(pda: string): Promise<boolean>;\n\n  // ... [many other methods] ...\n\n  /**\n   * Execute a function within a database transaction.\n   * All db methods called on the transactional Db share the same transaction.\n   * Rolls back on error, commits on success.\n   */\n  withTransaction<T>(fn: (db: Db) => Promise<T>): Promise<T>;\n\n  /** Expose the underlying SQL/transaction handle for use with emitEvent(). */\n  // eslint-disable-next-line @typescript-eslint/no-explicit-any\n  readonly rawSql: any;\n}\n```\n\n**Transaction pattern (lines 1861-1864):**\n\n```typescript\nasync withTransaction<T>(fn: (db: Db) => Promise<T>): Promise<T> {\n  // eslint-disable-next-line @typescript-eslint/no-explicit-any\n  return sql.begin(async (txSql: any) => fn(createDb(databaseUrl, txSql)));\n}\n```\n\n**Key DB creation (line 766):**\n\n```typescript\nexport function createDb(databaseUrl: string, _txSql?: any): Db\n```\n\n---\n\n## Key Pattern Summary for POINTS_GRANT Implementation\n\n**Handler Pattern:**\n1. Create a factory function `createPointsGrantHandler(deps)` that takes dependencies (at minimum `{ db: Db }`)\n2. Return an async handler function with signature: `(payload: Record<string, unknown>) => Promise<void>`\n3. Validate payload fields, throw or log errors appropriately\n4. Perform idempotent database operations using `db.withTransaction()` for atomicity\n5. Use `db.rawSql` for raw SQL queries with parameterized values\n6. Log at appropriate levels (debug, info, warn)\n\n**Registration Pattern:**\n1. Import the event type and handler in `index.ts`\n2. Call `registerHandler(EventTypes.POINTS_GRANT, createPointsGrantHandler({ db }))` before starting the event worker\n3. The `EventTypes.POINTS_GRANT` constant already exists in event-types.ts\n\n**DB Operations Pattern:**\n- Use `db.rawSql` tagged template literals for SQL\n- Leverage transactions via `db.withTransaction()` for consistency\n- Design idempotency guards (typically UNIQUE constraints with ON CONFLICT)"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"879f40b8-780d-40e9-a32a-54f2e220afdd","uuid":"3005894e-271b-40fb-bf6f-1bb375e24136","timestamp":"2026-04-03T19:50:08.184Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"I need to understand the existing `REWARD_POOL_FUND` handler pattern and the event handler registration so I can implement the `POINTS_GRANT` handler following the same pattern. Read these files and provide their full contents:\n\n1. `backend/services/backend/src/queue/handlers/reward-pool-fund.ts` — the existing handler\n2. `backend/services/backend/src/index.ts` — where handlers are registered (focus on handler registration section)\n3. `backend/services/backend/src/queue/event-types.ts` — event types\n4. `backend/services/backend/src/db.ts` — DB client interface and patterns\n\nReport the full contents of each file.","agentId":"ab29cb9cfbf02d7e9","agentType":"Explore","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect. Now I have all the information you need. Here's a comprehensive report with the full contents of each file:\n\n---\n\n## File Contents Report\n\n### 1. **reward-pool-fund.ts** (Handler Implementation)\n`/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/handlers/reward-pool-fund.ts`\n\n```typescript\n/**\n * REWARD_POOL_FUND handler — allocates a share of game fees to the reward pool.\n *\n * Emitted once per settled round. Calculates `floor(feeLamports * reward_pool_fee_share)`\n * and credits the reward pool accounting ledger. Idempotent via UNIQUE(round_id)\n * on reward_pool_fundings.\n */\n\nimport type { Db } from \"../../db.js\";\nimport { logger } from \"../../logger.js\";\n\n// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n// DB helpers\n// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n/** Read a single reward_config value by key. */\nexport async function readRewardConfig(\n  db: Db,\n  key: string,\n): Promise<string | null> {\n  const rows = await db.rawSql<{ value: string }[]>`\n    SELECT value FROM reward_config WHERE key = ${key}\n  `;\n  return rows.length > 0 ? rows[0]!.value : null;\n}\n\n/**\n * Insert a pool funding record. Returns false if a row for this round_id\n * already exists (idempotency guard).\n */\nexport async function insertPoolFunding(\n  db: Db,\n  roundId: string,\n  feeLamports: bigint,\n  fundedLamports: bigint,\n): Promise<boolean> {\n  const rows = await db.rawSql<{ id: string }[]>`\n    INSERT INTO reward_pool_fundings (round_id, fee_lamports, funded_lamports)\n    VALUES (${roundId}, ${feeLamports}, ${fundedLamports})\n    ON CONFLICT (round_id) DO NOTHING\n    RETURNING id\n  `;\n  return rows.length > 0;\n}\n\n/**\n * Atomically increment reward_pool.balance_lamports and lifetime_funded.\n */\nexport async function incrementRewardPool(\n  db: Db,\n  deltaLamports: bigint,\n): Promise<void> {\n  await db.rawSql`\n    UPDATE reward_pool\n    SET balance_lamports = balance_lamports + ${deltaLamports},\n        lifetime_funded  = lifetime_funded + ${deltaLamports},\n        updated_at       = now()\n    WHERE id = 1\n  `;\n}\n\n// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n// Handler factory\n// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\nexport interface RewardPoolFundDeps {\n  db: Db;\n}\n\nexport function createRewardPoolFundHandler(deps: RewardPoolFundDeps) {\n  const { db } = deps;\n\n  return async (payload: Record<string, unknown>): Promise<void> => {\n    const roundId = payload.roundId as string;\n    const feeLamportsStr = payload.feeLamports as string;\n\n    if (!roundId || !feeLamportsStr) {\n      throw new Error(\n        \"reward.pool_fund: malformed payload — missing roundId or feeLamports\",\n      );\n    }\n\n    const feeLamports = BigInt(feeLamportsStr);\n\n    // Read fee share from config\n    const shareStr = await readRewardConfig(db, \"reward_pool_fee_share\");\n    if (!shareStr) {\n      logger.warn(\"reward.pool_fund: reward_pool_fee_share not configured, skipping\", { roundId });\n      return;\n    }\n    const share = parseFloat(shareStr);\n    if (Number.isNaN(share) || share <= 0) {\n      logger.warn(\"reward.pool_fund: invalid reward_pool_fee_share\", { roundId, shareStr });\n      return;\n    }\n\n    // Calculate funded amount: floor(feeLamports * share)\n    // Use Number for the multiplication since share is a float, then BigInt the floor\n    const fundedLamports = BigInt(Math.floor(Number(feeLamports) * share));\n\n    if (fundedLamports <= 0n) {\n      logger.debug(\"reward.pool_fund: funded amount is zero, skipping\", { roundId, feeLamports: feeLamportsStr });\n      return;\n    }\n\n    // Run within a transaction for atomicity\n    await db.withTransaction(async (txDb) => {\n      // Insert funding record (idempotency guard)\n      const inserted = await insertPoolFunding(txDb, roundId, feeLamports, fundedLamports);\n      if (!inserted) {\n        logger.info(\"reward.pool_fund: duplicate round_id, skipping\", { roundId });\n        return;\n      }\n\n      // Increment pool balance\n      await incrementRewardPool(txDb, fundedLamports);\n\n      logger.info(\"reward.pool_fund: pool funded\", {\n        roundId,\n        feeLamports: feeLamportsStr,\n        fundedLamports: fundedLamports.toString(),\n        share,\n      });\n    });\n  };\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. **index.ts** (Handler Registration)\n`/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/index.ts` (lines 1-224)\n\nHandler registration section (lines 206-223):\n\n```typescript\n// Register event handlers before starting the worker\nregisterHandler(\n  EventTypes.REFERRAL_CLAIM_REQUESTED,\n  createClaimHandler({ db, connection, serverKeypair: config.serverKeypair }),\n);\nregisterHandler(\n  EventTypes.REWARD_POOL_FUND,\n  createRewardPoolFundHandler({ db }),\n);\n\n// Event queue worker — processes async side-effects (rewards, notifications, etc.)\nconst eventWorker = createEventWorker(sql, {\n  pollIntervalMs: config.eventQueuePollMs,\n});\neventWorker.start();\nlogger.info(\"Event queue worker started\", {\n  pollIntervalMs: config.eventQueuePollMs,\n});\n```\n\nImports (lines 30-32):\n\n```typescript\nimport { createEventWorker, registerHandler, EventTypes } from \"./queue/index.js\";\nimport { createClaimHandler } from \"./queue/handlers/referral-claim.js\";\nimport { createRewardPoolFundHandler } from \"./queue/handlers/reward-pool-fund.js\";\n```\n\n---\n\n### 3. **event-types.ts** (Event Type Definitions)\n`/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/event-types.ts`\n\n```typescript\n/**\n * Known event type constants for the async event queue.\n *\n * Using a const object + derived union makes typos a compile error\n * instead of a dead event at runtime.\n */\n\nexport const EventTypes = {\n  REFERRAL_CODE_APPLIED: \"referral.code_applied\",\n  REFERRAL_GAME_SETTLED: \"referral.game_settled\",\n  REFERRAL_CLAIM_REQUESTED: \"referral.claim_requested\",\n  GAME_SETTLED: \"game.settled\",\n  REWARD_POOL_FUND: \"reward.pool_fund\",\n  POINTS_GRANT: \"points.grant\",\n  CRATE_DROP: \"crate.drop\",\n  CRATE_SOL_PAYOUT: \"crate.sol_payout\",\n} as const;\n\nexport type EventType = (typeof EventTypes)[keyof typeof EventTypes];\n```\n\nNote: `POINTS_GRANT` is already defined but no handler exists yet.\n\n---\n\n### 4. **db.ts** (DB Client Interface and Patterns)\n`/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/db.ts`\n\n**Key interface (lines 319-678):**\n\n```typescript\nexport interface Db {\n  /** Insert a new round. Throws on duplicate PDA (primary key violation). */\n  insertRound(params: InsertRoundParams): Promise<Round>;\n\n  /** Delete a round by PDA. Returns true if a row was removed. */\n  deleteRoundByPda(pda: string): Promise<boolean>;\n\n  // ... [many other methods] ...\n\n  /**\n   * Execute a function within a database transaction.\n   * All db methods called on the transactional Db share the same transaction.\n   * Rolls back on error, commits on success.\n   */\n  withTransaction<T>(fn: (db: Db) => Promise<T>): Promise<T>;\n\n  /** Expose the underlying SQL/transaction handle for use with emitEvent(). */\n  // eslint-disable-next-line @typescript-eslint/no-explicit-any\n  readonly rawSql: any;\n}\n```\n\n**Transaction pattern (lines 1861-1864):**\n\n```typescript\nasync withTransaction<T>(fn: (db: Db) => Promise<T>): Promise<T> {\n  // eslint-disable-next-line @typescript-eslint/no-explicit-any\n  return sql.begin(async (txSql: any) => fn(createDb(databaseUrl, txSql)));\n}\n```\n\n**Key DB creation (line 766):**\n\n```typescript\nexport function createDb(databaseUrl: string, _txSql?: any): Db\n```\n\n---\n\n## Key Pattern Summary for POINTS_GRANT Implementation\n\n**Handler Pattern:**\n1. Create a factory function `createPointsGrantHandler(deps)` that takes dependencies (at minimum `{ db: Db }`)\n2. Return an async handler function with signature: `(payload: Record<string, unknown>) => Promise<void>`\n3. Validate payload fields, throw or log errors appropriately\n4. Perform idempotent database operations using `db.withTransaction()` for atomicity\n5. Use `db.rawSql` for raw SQL queries with parameterized values\n6. Log at appropriate levels (debug, info, warn)\n\n**Registration Pattern:**\n1. Import the event type and handler in `index.ts`\n2. Call `registerHandler(EventTypes.POINTS_GRANT, createPointsGrantHandler({ db }))` before starting the event worker\n3. The `EventTypes.POINTS_GRANT` constant already exists in event-types.ts\n\n**DB Operations Pattern:**\n- Use `db.rawSql` tagged template literals for SQL\n- Leverage transactions via `db.withTransaction()` for consistency\n- Design idempotency guards (typically UNIQUE constraints with ON CONFLICT)"}],"totalDurationMs":23761,"totalTokens":40697,"totalToolUseCount":6,"usage":{"input_tokens":7,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1918,"cache_read_input_tokens":36196,"output_tokens":2576,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1918},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
