{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01MTNmYokGVAnK87A22XpGfC","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information needed. Let me create a comprehensive report.\n\n## Integration Test Patterns & SOL/USD Price Service — Findings Report\n\n### 1. Integration Test Patterns (REWARD_POOL_FUND Test)\n\n**File:** `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/__tests__/integration.test.ts`\n\n#### Test Setup Architecture\n\nThe integration test uses a **MockConnection** class that simulates Solana on-chain state:\n- In-memory account storage (`Map<string, AccountData>`)\n- Simulated slot tracking for block height progression\n- Methods: `getAccountInfo()`, `getProgramAccounts()`, `sendRawTransaction()`, `confirmTransaction()`, `getLatestBlockhash()`\n\n#### Database Setup\n- Uses `makeSql()` helper to connect to real PostgreSQL (prefers `DATABASE_URL` env var, falls back to Unix socket at `/var/run/postgresql`)\n- `createDb()` wraps the postgres connection for typed queries\n- Pre-test cleanup via `TRUNCATE` and `UPDATE reward_pool SET balance_lamports = 0`\n\n#### JWT Authentication Pattern\n```typescript\nasync function makeJwt(wallet: string, userId = userIdFromWallet(wallet)) {\n  const now = Math.floor(Date.now() / 1000);\n  return new SignJWT({ wallet })\n    .setProtectedHeader({ alg: \"HS256\" })\n    .setSubject(userId)\n    .setIssuedAt(now)\n    .setExpirationTime(now + 3600)\n    .sign(JWT_SECRET);  // TextEncoder.encode(\"test-secret-for-integration-tests\")\n}\n```\n\n#### REWARD_POOL_FUND Test Pattern (Lines 1276-1346)\n\n**Key Steps:**\n1. **Precondition verification** — Ensure `reward_pool_fee_share` config exists (re-seed if `TRUNCATE` removed it):\n   ```typescript\n   const configRows = await rawSql`SELECT value FROM reward_config WHERE key = 'reward_pool_fee_share'`;\n   if (configRows.length === 0) {\n     await rawSql`INSERT INTO reward_config (key, value) VALUES ('reward_pool_fee_share', '0.20')`;\n   }\n   ```\n\n2. **Initial state check** — Verify pool starts at zero:\n   ```typescript\n   const poolBefore = await rawSql`SELECT balance_lamports, lifetime_funded FROM reward_pool WHERE id = 1`;\n   expect(BigInt(poolBefore[0]!.balance_lamports)).toBe(0n);\n   ```\n\n3. **Handler instantiation** — Create handler with dependency injection:\n   ```typescript\n   const handler = createRewardPoolFundHandler({ db });\n   ```\n\n4. **Event emission** — Call handler directly with payload:\n   ```typescript\n   await handler({\n     roundId: \"test-round-pool-fund-001\",\n     feeLamports: \"500000\"\n   });\n   ```\n\n5. **Assertion chain** — Verify:\n   - `reward_pool_fundings` row inserted with correct fee/funded amounts (idempotency key on `round_id`)\n   - `reward_pool.balance_lamports` incremented correctly\n   - `reward_pool.lifetime_funded` updated\n\n6. **Idempotency test** — Re-emit same `roundId`, verify no duplicate funding row and pool balance unchanged\n\n---\n\n### 2. SOL/USD Price Service\n\n**File:** `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/routes/price.ts`\n\n#### Implementation Details\n\n**Pyth Hermes Integration:**\n```typescript\nconst SOL_USD_FEED_ID = \"0xef0d8b6fda2ceba41da15d4095d1da392a0d2f8ed0c6c7bc0f4cfac8c280b56d\";\nconst CACHE_TTL_MS = 60_000; // 60 seconds\nconst client = new HermesClient(\"https://hermes.pyth.network\", {});\n```\n\n**Fetch Function:**\n```typescript\nasync function fetchSolPrice(): Promise<CachedPrice | null> {\n  if (cached && Date.now() - cached.fetchedAt < CACHE_TTL_MS) {\n    return cached;  // Return cached if fresh\n  }\n\n  try {\n    const updates = await client.getLatestPriceUpdates([SOL_USD_FEED_ID], {\n      encoding: \"base64\",\n      parsed: true,\n    });\n    const feed = updates.parsed?.[0];\n    if (!feed?.price) return cached;\n\n    const price = Number(feed.price.price) * Math.pow(10, feed.price.expo);\n    const updatedAt = new Date(feed.price.publish_time * 1000).toISOString();\n\n    cached = { price, updatedAt, fetchedAt: Date.now() };\n    return cached;\n  } catch (err) {\n    logger.warn(\"hermes: SOL/USD fetch failed\", { error: err.message });\n    return cached;  // Return stale cache on error\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Endpoint:**\n```typescript\nexport function createPriceRoutes() {\n  const app = new Hono();\n  \n  app.get(\"/sol-usd\", async (c) => {\n    const result = await fetchSolPrice();\n    if (!result) {\n      return c.json({ error: \"Price unavailable\" }, 503);\n    }\n    return c.json({\n      price: result.price,\n      updatedAt: result.updatedAt,\n    });\n  });\n  \n  return app;\n}\n```\n\n**Mounted in main app** (`/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/index.ts:261`):\n```typescript\napp.route(\"/price\", createPriceRoutes());\n```\n\n**Cache Strategy:**\n- 60-second TTL with `fetchedAt` timestamp tracking\n- Degraded mode: returns stale cache on network errors\n- No cache returned if network fails on first fetch\n\n#### For POINTS_GRANT Handler\n\nThe SOL/USD price endpoint is **publicly accessible at `/price/sol-usd`**. To use it in the `POINTS_GRANT` handler:\n- Call `fetchSolPrice()` directly (if handler and price module share scope) or\n- Make an HTTP fetch within the handler to `http://localhost:3000/price/sol-usd` (production host)\n\n**Related reward_config keys** for points calculation (from migration):\n```sql\nINSERT INTO reward_config (key, value) VALUES\n  ('points_per_dollar', '500'),\n  ('points_crate_drop_rate', '0.05'),\n  ('sol_crate_drop_rate', '0.01'),\n  ('sol_crate_pool_pct', '0.10'),\n  ('sol_crate_min_value', '10000000'),\n  ('points_crate_min', '500'),\n  ('points_crate_max', '5000');\n```\n\n---\n\n### 3. Database Schema — Challenge Engine & Reward Tables\n\n**Migration File:** `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/migrations/011_challenge_engine.sql`\n\n#### Key Tables for POINTS_GRANT\n\n**`player_points`** — Player point balances (lines 11-17)\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE player_points (\n  user_id             TEXT PRIMARY KEY,\n  wallet              TEXT NOT NULL UNIQUE,\n  balance             BIGINT NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,\n  lifetime_earned     BIGINT NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,\n  updated_at          TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now()\n);\n```\n\n**`point_grants`** — Immutable point grant ledger (lines 20-32)\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE point_grants (\n  id                  BIGINT GENERATED ALWAYS AS IDENTITY PRIMARY KEY,\n  user_id             TEXT NOT NULL,\n  wallet              TEXT NOT NULL,\n  source_type         TEXT NOT NULL CHECK (source_type IN ('wager', 'challenge_completed', 'bonus_completed', 'crate_points')),\n  source_id           TEXT NOT NULL,\n  amount              BIGINT NOT NULL,\n  metadata            JSONB NOT NULL DEFAULT '{}',\n  created_at          TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now(),\n  UNIQUE (user_id, source_type, source_id)\n);\nCREATE INDEX idx_point_grants_user_created ON point_grants (user_id, created_at DESC);\n```\n\n**`reward_config`** — Operator-tunable parameters (lines 4-8)\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE reward_config (\n  key         TEXT PRIMARY KEY,\n  value       TEXT NOT NULL,\n  updated_at  TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now()\n);\n```\n\n**`dogpile_events`** — Multiplier events for bonus periods (lines 166-176)\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE dogpile_events (\n  id              BIGINT GENERATED ALWAYS AS IDENTITY PRIMARY KEY,\n  campaign_id     BIGINT REFERENCES campaigns(id),\n  starts_at       TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL,\n  ends_at         TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL,\n  multiplier      NUMERIC(4,2) NOT NULL DEFAULT 2.0,\n  status          TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'scheduled' CHECK (status IN ('scheduled', 'active', 'ended', 'cancelled')),\n  created_at      TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now()\n);\nCREATE INDEX idx_dogpile_active ON dogpile_events (status, starts_at, ends_at) WHERE status IN ('scheduled', 'active');\n```\n\n#### Idempotency Pattern\nThe `point_grants` table uses **`UNIQUE (user_id, source_type, source_id)`** to enforce idempotency — re-processing the same grant source is a no-op (similar to REWARD_POOL_FUND).\n\n---\n\n### 4. Event Handler Registration Pattern\n\n**Files:** `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/handler-registry.ts` and `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/index.ts`\n\n**Handler Registration (lines 207-214 of index.ts):**\n```typescript\nregisterHandler(\n  EventTypes.REFERRAL_CLAIM_REQUESTED,\n  createClaimHandler({ db, connection, serverKeypair: config.serverKeypair }),\n);\nregisterHandler(\n  EventTypes.REWARD_POOL_FUND,\n  createRewardPoolFundHandler({ db }),\n);\n```\n\n**Event Types** (`/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/event-types.ts`):\n```typescript\nexport const EventTypes = {\n  REFERRAL_CODE_APPLIED: \"referral.code_applied\",\n  REFERRAL_GAME_SETTLED: \"referral.game_settled\",\n  REFERRAL_CLAIM_REQUESTED: \"referral.claim_requested\",\n  GAME_SETTLED: \"game.settled\",\n  REWARD_POOL_FUND: \"reward.pool_fund\",\n  POINTS_GRANT: \"points.grant\",\n  CRATE_DROP: \"crate.drop\",\n  CRATE_SOL_PAYOUT: \"crate.sol_payout\",\n};\n```\n\n**Handler Factory Pattern** (from `reward-pool-fund.ts`):\n```typescript\nexport interface RewardPoolFundDeps {\n  db: Db;\n}\n\nexport function createRewardPoolFundHandler(deps: RewardPoolFundDeps) {\n  const { db } = deps;\n  return async (payload: Record<string, unknown>): Promise<void> => {\n    // Handler logic here\n  };\n}\n```\n\n**For POINTS_GRANT:** Create handler at `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/handlers/points-grant.ts` with similar pattern, then register in `index.ts` before `eventWorker.start()`."}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"879f40b8-780d-40e9-a32a-54f2e220afdd","uuid":"0484cebe-ecb9-47dc-b3bc-e504ddc816f5","timestamp":"2026-04-03T19:51:07.857Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"I need to understand the integration test patterns and how to get SOL/USD price for the POINTS_GRANT handler. \n\n1. Read `backend/services/backend/src/__tests__/integration.test.ts` — focus on the REWARD_POOL_FUND test and how test setup works (db helpers, event emission, etc.)\n2. Search for any existing SOL/USD price service or endpoint in the backend codebase. Look for files mentioning \"price\", \"sol-usd\", \"solPrice\", or \"usd\". Check routes, services, and any price fetching code.\n3. Read the migration file `backend/services/backend/migrations/011_challenge_engine.sql` — specifically the `player_points`, `point_grants`, `reward_config`, and `dogpile_events` table definitions.\n\nReport findings with relevant code snippets.","agentId":"af581febb9f4e1644","agentType":"Explore","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information needed. Let me create a comprehensive report.\n\n## Integration Test Patterns & SOL/USD Price Service — Findings Report\n\n### 1. Integration Test Patterns (REWARD_POOL_FUND Test)\n\n**File:** `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/__tests__/integration.test.ts`\n\n#### Test Setup Architecture\n\nThe integration test uses a **MockConnection** class that simulates Solana on-chain state:\n- In-memory account storage (`Map<string, AccountData>`)\n- Simulated slot tracking for block height progression\n- Methods: `getAccountInfo()`, `getProgramAccounts()`, `sendRawTransaction()`, `confirmTransaction()`, `getLatestBlockhash()`\n\n#### Database Setup\n- Uses `makeSql()` helper to connect to real PostgreSQL (prefers `DATABASE_URL` env var, falls back to Unix socket at `/var/run/postgresql`)\n- `createDb()` wraps the postgres connection for typed queries\n- Pre-test cleanup via `TRUNCATE` and `UPDATE reward_pool SET balance_lamports = 0`\n\n#### JWT Authentication Pattern\n```typescript\nasync function makeJwt(wallet: string, userId = userIdFromWallet(wallet)) {\n  const now = Math.floor(Date.now() / 1000);\n  return new SignJWT({ wallet })\n    .setProtectedHeader({ alg: \"HS256\" })\n    .setSubject(userId)\n    .setIssuedAt(now)\n    .setExpirationTime(now + 3600)\n    .sign(JWT_SECRET);  // TextEncoder.encode(\"test-secret-for-integration-tests\")\n}\n```\n\n#### REWARD_POOL_FUND Test Pattern (Lines 1276-1346)\n\n**Key Steps:**\n1. **Precondition verification** — Ensure `reward_pool_fee_share` config exists (re-seed if `TRUNCATE` removed it):\n   ```typescript\n   const configRows = await rawSql`SELECT value FROM reward_config WHERE key = 'reward_pool_fee_share'`;\n   if (configRows.length === 0) {\n     await rawSql`INSERT INTO reward_config (key, value) VALUES ('reward_pool_fee_share', '0.20')`;\n   }\n   ```\n\n2. **Initial state check** — Verify pool starts at zero:\n   ```typescript\n   const poolBefore = await rawSql`SELECT balance_lamports, lifetime_funded FROM reward_pool WHERE id = 1`;\n   expect(BigInt(poolBefore[0]!.balance_lamports)).toBe(0n);\n   ```\n\n3. **Handler instantiation** — Create handler with dependency injection:\n   ```typescript\n   const handler = createRewardPoolFundHandler({ db });\n   ```\n\n4. **Event emission** — Call handler directly with payload:\n   ```typescript\n   await handler({\n     roundId: \"test-round-pool-fund-001\",\n     feeLamports: \"500000\"\n   });\n   ```\n\n5. **Assertion chain** — Verify:\n   - `reward_pool_fundings` row inserted with correct fee/funded amounts (idempotency key on `round_id`)\n   - `reward_pool.balance_lamports` incremented correctly\n   - `reward_pool.lifetime_funded` updated\n\n6. **Idempotency test** — Re-emit same `roundId`, verify no duplicate funding row and pool balance unchanged\n\n---\n\n### 2. SOL/USD Price Service\n\n**File:** `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/routes/price.ts`\n\n#### Implementation Details\n\n**Pyth Hermes Integration:**\n```typescript\nconst SOL_USD_FEED_ID = \"0xef0d8b6fda2ceba41da15d4095d1da392a0d2f8ed0c6c7bc0f4cfac8c280b56d\";\nconst CACHE_TTL_MS = 60_000; // 60 seconds\nconst client = new HermesClient(\"https://hermes.pyth.network\", {});\n```\n\n**Fetch Function:**\n```typescript\nasync function fetchSolPrice(): Promise<CachedPrice | null> {\n  if (cached && Date.now() - cached.fetchedAt < CACHE_TTL_MS) {\n    return cached;  // Return cached if fresh\n  }\n\n  try {\n    const updates = await client.getLatestPriceUpdates([SOL_USD_FEED_ID], {\n      encoding: \"base64\",\n      parsed: true,\n    });\n    const feed = updates.parsed?.[0];\n    if (!feed?.price) return cached;\n\n    const price = Number(feed.price.price) * Math.pow(10, feed.price.expo);\n    const updatedAt = new Date(feed.price.publish_time * 1000).toISOString();\n\n    cached = { price, updatedAt, fetchedAt: Date.now() };\n    return cached;\n  } catch (err) {\n    logger.warn(\"hermes: SOL/USD fetch failed\", { error: err.message });\n    return cached;  // Return stale cache on error\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Endpoint:**\n```typescript\nexport function createPriceRoutes() {\n  const app = new Hono();\n  \n  app.get(\"/sol-usd\", async (c) => {\n    const result = await fetchSolPrice();\n    if (!result) {\n      return c.json({ error: \"Price unavailable\" }, 503);\n    }\n    return c.json({\n      price: result.price,\n      updatedAt: result.updatedAt,\n    });\n  });\n  \n  return app;\n}\n```\n\n**Mounted in main app** (`/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/index.ts:261`):\n```typescript\napp.route(\"/price\", createPriceRoutes());\n```\n\n**Cache Strategy:**\n- 60-second TTL with `fetchedAt` timestamp tracking\n- Degraded mode: returns stale cache on network errors\n- No cache returned if network fails on first fetch\n\n#### For POINTS_GRANT Handler\n\nThe SOL/USD price endpoint is **publicly accessible at `/price/sol-usd`**. To use it in the `POINTS_GRANT` handler:\n- Call `fetchSolPrice()` directly (if handler and price module share scope) or\n- Make an HTTP fetch within the handler to `http://localhost:3000/price/sol-usd` (production host)\n\n**Related reward_config keys** for points calculation (from migration):\n```sql\nINSERT INTO reward_config (key, value) VALUES\n  ('points_per_dollar', '500'),\n  ('points_crate_drop_rate', '0.05'),\n  ('sol_crate_drop_rate', '0.01'),\n  ('sol_crate_pool_pct', '0.10'),\n  ('sol_crate_min_value', '10000000'),\n  ('points_crate_min', '500'),\n  ('points_crate_max', '5000');\n```\n\n---\n\n### 3. Database Schema — Challenge Engine & Reward Tables\n\n**Migration File:** `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/migrations/011_challenge_engine.sql`\n\n#### Key Tables for POINTS_GRANT\n\n**`player_points`** — Player point balances (lines 11-17)\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE player_points (\n  user_id             TEXT PRIMARY KEY,\n  wallet              TEXT NOT NULL UNIQUE,\n  balance             BIGINT NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,\n  lifetime_earned     BIGINT NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,\n  updated_at          TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now()\n);\n```\n\n**`point_grants`** — Immutable point grant ledger (lines 20-32)\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE point_grants (\n  id                  BIGINT GENERATED ALWAYS AS IDENTITY PRIMARY KEY,\n  user_id             TEXT NOT NULL,\n  wallet              TEXT NOT NULL,\n  source_type         TEXT NOT NULL CHECK (source_type IN ('wager', 'challenge_completed', 'bonus_completed', 'crate_points')),\n  source_id           TEXT NOT NULL,\n  amount              BIGINT NOT NULL,\n  metadata            JSONB NOT NULL DEFAULT '{}',\n  created_at          TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now(),\n  UNIQUE (user_id, source_type, source_id)\n);\nCREATE INDEX idx_point_grants_user_created ON point_grants (user_id, created_at DESC);\n```\n\n**`reward_config`** — Operator-tunable parameters (lines 4-8)\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE reward_config (\n  key         TEXT PRIMARY KEY,\n  value       TEXT NOT NULL,\n  updated_at  TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now()\n);\n```\n\n**`dogpile_events`** — Multiplier events for bonus periods (lines 166-176)\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE dogpile_events (\n  id              BIGINT GENERATED ALWAYS AS IDENTITY PRIMARY KEY,\n  campaign_id     BIGINT REFERENCES campaigns(id),\n  starts_at       TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL,\n  ends_at         TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL,\n  multiplier      NUMERIC(4,2) NOT NULL DEFAULT 2.0,\n  status          TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'scheduled' CHECK (status IN ('scheduled', 'active', 'ended', 'cancelled')),\n  created_at      TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now()\n);\nCREATE INDEX idx_dogpile_active ON dogpile_events (status, starts_at, ends_at) WHERE status IN ('scheduled', 'active');\n```\n\n#### Idempotency Pattern\nThe `point_grants` table uses **`UNIQUE (user_id, source_type, source_id)`** to enforce idempotency — re-processing the same grant source is a no-op (similar to REWARD_POOL_FUND).\n\n---\n\n### 4. Event Handler Registration Pattern\n\n**Files:** `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/handler-registry.ts` and `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/index.ts`\n\n**Handler Registration (lines 207-214 of index.ts):**\n```typescript\nregisterHandler(\n  EventTypes.REFERRAL_CLAIM_REQUESTED,\n  createClaimHandler({ db, connection, serverKeypair: config.serverKeypair }),\n);\nregisterHandler(\n  EventTypes.REWARD_POOL_FUND,\n  createRewardPoolFundHandler({ db }),\n);\n```\n\n**Event Types** (`/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/event-types.ts`):\n```typescript\nexport const EventTypes = {\n  REFERRAL_CODE_APPLIED: \"referral.code_applied\",\n  REFERRAL_GAME_SETTLED: \"referral.game_settled\",\n  REFERRAL_CLAIM_REQUESTED: \"referral.claim_requested\",\n  GAME_SETTLED: \"game.settled\",\n  REWARD_POOL_FUND: \"reward.pool_fund\",\n  POINTS_GRANT: \"points.grant\",\n  CRATE_DROP: \"crate.drop\",\n  CRATE_SOL_PAYOUT: \"crate.sol_payout\",\n};\n```\n\n**Handler Factory Pattern** (from `reward-pool-fund.ts`):\n```typescript\nexport interface RewardPoolFundDeps {\n  db: Db;\n}\n\nexport function createRewardPoolFundHandler(deps: RewardPoolFundDeps) {\n  const { db } = deps;\n  return async (payload: Record<string, unknown>): Promise<void> => {\n    // Handler logic here\n  };\n}\n```\n\n**For POINTS_GRANT:** Create handler at `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/handlers/points-grant.ts` with similar pattern, then register in `index.ts` before `eventWorker.start()`."}],"totalDurationMs":78377,"totalTokens":60388,"totalToolUseCount":27,"usage":{"input_tokens":5,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4336,"cache_read_input_tokens":53104,"output_tokens":2943,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":4336},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
